{{Han etym}}

{{liushu|p}}. Possible interpretations:
* The sepal of a flower; original form of {{och-l|蒂|stem; peduncle}}. {{attn|zh|may need explanation of why this may be unlikely http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_4b41fa86010165ca.html}}
* Tied-up [[firewood]]; original form of {{och-l|禘}}.
* An altar; original form of {{och-l|禘}}.

The character was later borrowed for “God of Heaven”, which was later used as a title for emperors. ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously interprets the character to be a {{Han compound|丄|朿|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=up; above|nocap=1}}.
